comments.content: Family of nitric oxide synthases
Also known as GUCY1B3 [uniprot:Q02153].
There are four soluble Guanylate cyclasdes (sGCs) encoded in the human genome: GUCY1A1, GUCY1A2, GUCY1B1, and GUCY1B2.
NOS3 is implicated in vascular smooth muscle relaxation through cGMP [PMID:1378832,PMID:20590592].
Also known as GUCY1A3 [uniprot:Q02108].
Alternative name is PGC1A [uniprot:Q9UBK2]
Inhibition of cGMP degradation by PDE5 increases cGMP availability [PMID:9714779].
AKT family of serine/threonine-protein kinases

Were presumed to have redundant roles, but more recent research indicated uisform specific functions in cellular events. AKT1 is more specifically involved in cellular survival pathways, by inhibiting apoptotic processes; whereas AKT2 is more specific for the insulin receptor signaling pathway. Moreover, while AKT1 and AKT2 are often implicated in many aspects of cellular transformation, the 2 isoforms act in a complementary opposing manner. The role of AKT3 is less clear, though it appears to be predominantly expressed in brain. [PMID:24039187]
Glycogen synthase kinase 3beta (GSK3beta) tideglusib (NP031112) has anti-inflammatory and neuroprotective properties [PMID:17522320].
There are 4 genes encoding soluble guanylyl cyclases (sGCs)
sCGs are nitric oxide receptors
AKT is activated through phosphorylation upon recruitement to the cell membrane
Negative regulation of neuronal death [GO:1901215]
Regulation of neuron projection development [GO:0010975]
An increase in cGMP leads to smooth muscle relaxation and therefore relieve the symptoms of erectile disfunction [PMID:2545495,PMID:8813924].
The family of nitric oxide synthases produce nitric oxide (NO) from L-argine, oxigen and NAPDH [PMID:1722402,PMID:1662386].
cGMP is converted into GMP through hydrolysis by PDE5 [PMID:7870041].
Transcriptional coactivator
GAPDH can bind AKT to limit dephosphorylation, prolonging AKT activity and therefor increase mitochondrial membrane potential stabilization [PMID:23645209].
The family of PDE4s (cAMP-specific 3',5'-cyclic phosphodiesterases) hydrolyse cAMP into AMP.
Inhibition of cGMP degradation by PDE5 increases cGMP availability [PMID:9714779].
Repressed transcription of PGC-1-alpha (PPARGC1A), thereby playing a role in regulation of neuron death [PMID:21376232]
Soluble guanylyl cyclases (sGC) are activated by nitric oxide (NO) [PMID:9742212].
The family of AKT proteins stabalize mitochondrial membrane potential through TCL1A [uniprot:P56279] and TCL1B [unirprot:O95988]. [PMID:10983986,PMID:11839817]
sGCs catalyze the conversion of GTP into GMP.
